json.title: Tata Sierra unveiled, Maruti eVitara launch date, and more | News | Autocar India
json.text:
In this week’s Autocar India Quick News, Tata has revealed the production-spec Sierra, while Maruti has confirmed the e-Vitara’s India launch for December 2. Audi has introduced new Signature Line versions of the Q3 and Q5, and Tata has updated the Curvv and Curvv EV with additional features. At the premium end, Porsche has launched the 2025 911 Turbo S, and Maserati has announced India prices for the GranTurismo, GranCabrio Folgore EVs and the Grecale Folgore. On two wheels, Yamaha has launched the XSR155 and FZ Rave, and also showcased the EC-06 and Aerox Electric scooters. Lenny D’sa has all the details.

json.title: Honda’s bold comeback plan | Deep Drive Podcast Ep. 86 | Autocar India
json.text:

json.title: Citroen Basalt X review – Updated interior now matches stylish exterior | First Drive |Autocar India
json.text:
Less than a year since launch, Citroen has updated the Basalt coupe SUV to revive its flagging sales. Dubbed the Basalt X, it finally gets the interior it always deserved, along with much-requested features such as cruise control and keyless entry. Citroen has also revised prices across the range, making it a far more enticing proposition. Lenny D’sa has the full review, including instrumented performance and real-world fuel efficiency tests.

Cameraperson - Mritunjay Chakraborty
Editor - Sanil Sawardekar
